# üéÆ Caballebrios One

A comprehensive game night tracking system built with Streamlit.

## Features

‚úÖ **Player Management** - Add players with profile pictures
‚úÖ **Season Tracking** - Create and manage multiple seasons with separate scoring
‚úÖ **Game Library** - Define games with custom point values and win conditions
‚úÖ **Game Night Recording** - Track multiple games, rounds, and winners per night
‚úÖ **Penalty System** - Record absence penalties and custom penalties
‚úÖ **Visual Reports** - Beautiful charts and statistics including:
- Season leaderboard
- Points progression over time
- Best game per player
- Game popularity analytics
- Win distribution
- Attendance tracking
- Penalty summaries

## Installation

1. Install dependencies:
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

2. Run the app:
```bash
streamlit run caballebrios_one.py
```

3. Open your browser to `http://localhost:8501`

## Quick Start Guide

### First Time Setup

1. **Add Players** - Go to the "Players" tab and add all your players
2. **Create a Season** - Go to "Seasons" tab and create your first season (mark as active)
3. **Add Games** - Go to "Games" tab and add all the games you play
4. **Configure Settings** - Set your default penalty amount in the code if needed (default: $10)

### Recording a Game Night

1. Go to **Game Nights** tab
2. Click "Record New Game Night" and set the date
3. For each game played:
   - Select the game
   - Enter round number (if playing multiple rounds)
   - Select winner(s) - multiple winners are supported!
4. Record any penalties for absent players

### Viewing Reports

Go to the **Reports** tab to see:
- Current leaderboard
- Points progression charts
- Player statistics
- Fun facts and insights

## Database

The app uses SQLite and stores data in `caballebrios.db` in your home directory. 

## Tips

- You can edit game point values and descriptions at any time
- Multiple winners per round are supported (great for team games!)
- Track multiple rounds of the same game on one night
- Custom penalties allow you to penalize players for other infractions beyond absence
- Export data by accessing the SQLite database directly

## Architecture

- **Frontend**: Streamlit with custom CSS
- **Backend**: SQLite database
- **Visualizations**: Plotly for interactive charts
- **Image Handling**: PIL for profile pictures

## Future Enhancements Ideas

- Export season reports to PDF
- Player head-to-head statistics
- Game recommendations based on play history
- Mobile-responsive design improvements
- Multi-season comparison reports

